uTube.";i:1;s:79:"10 Minute Beginner Chair Exercises for Seniors no equipment needed Watch later.";i:2;s:40:"Benefits of Chair Exercises for Seniors.";i:3;s:78:"Seated exercise offers all the benefits of standing exercise without the risk.";i:4;s:91:"Chair exercises will keep your joints flexible improving your range of motion and mobility.";i:5;s:125:"They also strengthen and stabilize your muscles resulting in improved balance which is key for preventing falls and injuries.";i:6;s:99:"If you are an exercise leader review pages 5 and 6 to see a brief description of all the exercises.";i:7;s:50:"When you are ready to start these chair exercises.";i:8;s:138:"For the first time go to Module A pages 7 to 13 and do the warm-up and exercises on several different occasions until you are comfortable.";i:9;s:70:"So unlike many workouts older adults can do it without any assistance.";i:10;s:124:"Perfect for stretching joints and tight muscles to ease the pain the chair workouts can be performed even while watching TV.";i:11;s:104:"From Seated Leg Lifts to standing toe raises the workouts are simply comforting for a person of old age.";i:12;s:81:"And this very aspect makes it one of the best workouts for seniors to do at home.";i:13;s:103:"Keeping your chest upright push your hips back and bend your knees to lower your body toward the chair.";i:14;s:53:"Either touch your bum to the chair or sit down on it.";i:15;s:201:"Exercise 4 Chair Marching First check your posture Lift alternate legs so that your feet lift about 2 inches from the floor and swing your arms forwards and back at a speed that is comfortable for you.";i:16;s:43:"Imagine you marching along at a brisk pace.";i:17;s:33:"Continue for about 20 30 seconds.";i:18;s:109:"Although doing chair exercises is intended for seniors younger people than seniors are also allowed to do it.";i:19;s:73:"There are no special specifications for the age of chair exercises users.";i:20;s:153:"For some people doing chair exercises has the benefit of easier to do a workout because as a tool to replace the existing gym equipment in the gym place.";i:21;s:104:"First sit upright towards the middle of the chair keeping your back from touching the back of the chair.";i:22;s:38:"Hold onto the sides of the chair seat.";i:23;s:28:"Keeping your knee bent lift.";i:24;s:90:"This 10 minute chair workout for seniors is a perfect way to gain strength and be healthy.";i:25;s:94:"HASfits seated exercise for seniors and chair exercises for the elderly requires no equipment.";i:26;s:144:"The seated workouts for seniors chair exercise for seniors and seated exercises for elderly can be done right from the comfort of your own home.";i:27;s:181:"Chair-bound exercises are ideal for people with lower body injuries or disabilities those with weight problems or diabetes and frail seniors looking to reduce their risk of falling.";i:28;s:204:"Cardiovascular and flexibility chair exercises can help improve posture and reduce back pain while any chair exercise can help alleviate body sores caused by sitting in the same position for long periods.";i:29;s:11:"Hi Im Mike.";i:30;s:60:"A Seniors Specialist Physiotherapist and Exercise Scientist.";i:31;s:138:"I have spent many years working with people over 60 in Australia and now all over the world to help them improve their health and fitness.";i:32;s:167:"If youre over 60 I have designed this website to give YOU everything you need for you to move better get stronger become fitter get healthier and look and feel better.";i:33;s:90:"This 10 minute chair workout for seniors is a perfect way to gain strength and be healthy.";i:34;s:94:"HASfits seated exercise for seniors and chair exercises for the elderly requires no equipment.";i:35;s:92:"The seated workouts for seniors chair exercise for seniors and seated exercises for elderly.";i:36;s:49:"13 Chair-based strength exercises no equipment 7.";i:37;s:21:"Sit to stand Purpose.";i:38;s:55:"This will strengthen muscles of your thighs and bottom.";i:39;s:156:"Take feet back slightly until knees are above the toes keep both heels on the floor place palms on your thighs just above the knees and fingers pointing in.";i:40;s:31:"For exercise chair for seniors.";i:41;s:90:"CHAIR EXERCISE DVD FOR SENIORS- Simply Seated is an invigorating Total Body Chair Workout.";i:42;s:51:"Warm up Aerobic Endurance Strengthening Stretching.";i:43;s:51:"You will love this chair exercise for seniors DVDs.";i:44;s:18:"44 out of 5 stars.";i:45;s:112:"Chair exercises are great for everyone including seniors and anyone looking for ways to stay active as they age.";i:46;s:70:"Learn about some seated and standing chair exercises for seniors here.";}}